d 'MULTISPLINE': module for spline-based nonlinear modeling for multilevel and longitudinal data
d
d  multispline fits nonlinear regression models using natural cubic
d  splines or B-splines, with optional multilevel random effects
d  via mixed. It provides a complete workflow: automatic knot/df
d  selection by AIC or BIC; cross-classified and nested multilevel
d  structures; Nakagawa-Schielzeth marginal and conditional
d  R-squared decomposition; first and second derivatives with
d  confidence bands; turning-point detection; model comparison
d  (linear vs polynomial vs spline); and inline publication plots
d  (trajectory, slope, curvature, combo). All functionality is
d  contained in a single .ado file with no external dependencies
d  beyond base Stata commands (regress, mixed, mkspline).
d
d KW: splines
d KW: nonlinear regression
d KW: multilevel models
d KW: natural cubic splines
d KW: longitudinal data
d KW: derivatives
d KW: turning points
d KW: model comparison
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260417
d
d Author: Subir Hait, Michigan State University
d Support: email haitsubi@@msu.edu
d
f multispline.ado
f multispline_plot.ado
f multispline.sthlp
f multispline_example.do
